<br>
 I have always been of the mindset (not sure if it came from this board or not) that buffing agility ONLY affects your AC. I've seen several threads (yes I used the search function) that show relativity between amount of AC and Agility.<br>
<br>
I am wondering, however, if agility affects damage mitigation or avoidance. I'm not talking about CA or CS, I'm just talking about that stupid buff we get called wrulan. If I give the main tank on a raid 60 agi, and his ac increases 5, will his damage avoidance or mitigation change above and beyond the 5 ac he gets from the buff?<br>
<br>
I've made it abundantly clear that I don't buff agi on raids. If someone says the damage reduction seen is worth 525 mana per group and constant tells for refreshes, I will change my outlook on the matter. Until then, I will consider that the shammy in my guild that says agi actually helps is merely having delusions and that it is nothing more than a placebo.<br>
<br>
Please help me clear this up, thank you in advance for your replies.<br>
<br>
